Only apply it once to an item, as a second application can make it 'super-grown' with negative value. Combine 'grown' items that share similar sizes (e.g., large with large) and habitats (e.g., land with land) for the safest and largest value increases. Combining 'grown' items of the same size but different habitats (like large land + large water) can also yield high values (up to 50). Avoid combining items with vastly different sizes or too many disparate habitats (land, air, water) as this consistently creates 'overcomplicated' items with severe negative values.
